			<div class="content" id="post-content-4555773">
									

<p>First, I want to say thank you for taking the time to help me to improve it. This was significantly more feedback than I expected, and I am sincerely grateful.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Critique&nbsp;response&nbsp;-&gt;</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>The first thing I did was go in and fix the fonts thing. I'd been struggling for a while to figure out how to insure the font imported across the [[include]], and I found it imported several different ways. The way you saw it showcased one of the various ways I found.</p>
<p>Your fix is tremendously more streamlined, and I have applied it.</p>
<p>I am not entirely certain which code is native only to BHL, that requires a much more intensive sit down than I have time for at the moment, but I fully intend to do a line by line comparison at some point.</p>
<p>I had a lot of trouble figuring out how to change the sidebar link color. A lot of those colors were native to BHL and I eventually was able to change them through assistance by Croqueambouche. I didn't clean up after myself, which is what you saw there. This has been remedied, and a: and a:visited are both the same now.</p>
<p>My blockquote code now looks like this:</p>
<div class="code">
<pre>
<code>   blockquote,
   .blockquote {
    color: rgb(var(--light-pale-gray-monochrome)); 
    border-radius: 10px; 
    border:dashed 1px rgb(var(--black-monochrome-alt)); 
    background: rgb(var(--dark-gray-monochrome)); 
   }</code>
</pre></div>
<p>Finally, I went through and made sure the entirety of my code lined up in a consistent manner. There are line breaks between sections for my own ease. Now that I know what most everything does, I have also removed all of the holdover quotes from BHL.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Again, thank you for your time. My last true learning code was back in 2004, give or take a few months. This has been an enlightening experience, despite the frustration. All I can do is apologize to you for my sloppy code and promise to do better as I move forward.</p>

							</div>

								
